Package parser

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ActionTable
    The ActionTable class is used to represent an ActionTable, it contains columns and rows used to access elements more easily in the action table.
    Parser
    This class is the main class, it represents the parser It contains various methods sued to parse and generate a Parse tree
    ParseTree
    A skeleton class to represent parse trees.
    Rules
    This class represents the rules It contains all the rules of the grammar
    Variable
    This class represents a variable It is used to know if a variable is a terminal or not and contains some useful methods
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    LexicalVariable
    Enum used to represents the different variables
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    InvalidSyntaxException
    Custom Error class used to represent an invalid Syntax This is thrown when we find an invalid syntax in the FORTR-S file
